Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa returned to Parliament for the question and answer session on Tuesday. This was the president's second question and answer session after he was elected president in February this year. Issues raised by MPs included whether he will launch an investigation into alleged corruption in state security and crime intelligence. READ: Arthur Fraser's promotion is worrisome, says Kasrils Responding to questions on Arthur Fraser's removal as head of the State Security Agency, the president said he was unable to give an answer as the matter was sub judice. Opposition MPs wanted to know why Fraser was transferred to Correctional Services. Ramaphosa said the DA’s court application prevented him from providing answers in Parliament. eNCA